{
  "texts": [
    "Authors in [93] proposed a method for debiasing and removing confounder vectors by employing a graph-based causality method to discover the relationship between an input feature, a concept, and a target class.",
    "Although interpretation methods can be used to identify confounded attributes [203,204], it is unclear how unobserved confounded attributes can be detected [86].",
    "Enhancing automatic concept generation methodsRecent interesting efforts for supervised concept interpretation tasks include Hierarchical CBM [90], PCBM [88], CBM-AUC [89], CBM [87], CAV [69], CBSD [92].",
    "However, because of their reliance on predefined concept annotation datasets, these methods are impractical for real-world problems.",
    "Creating concept annotations is an extremely expensive operation that frequently results in expert bias [89,98]."
  ]
}